The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 December is 141,849 (16,348.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 December, there were 9,131 new confirmed cases (1,052.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 December, there were 6,536 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 40% (2,595 extra cases).
